Privacy Policy for Open Kitchen

Last updated: June 2026

1. Data Controller
The data controller responsible for your personal data is:
Konstantin Brussig Email: support@healthyapp.info

2. Overview
This Privacy Policy explains how Open Kitchen (“the App”) collects, uses, and protects your information when you use the App.
By using Open Kitchen, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

3. Information We Collect
We collect and process the following types of data:

3.1 Account Information
When you create an account, we collect:
Unique user identifier (Firebase UID)
Email address (if using Google sign-in)
Profile information (e.g., username, profile picture)

3.2 Public Profile Data (“Kitchen”)
Your profile may be publicly visible and can include:
Username
Profile image
Description (if provided)
Activity related to recipes and interactions

3.3 User-Generated Content
We collect and store content you create in the App, including:
Recipes (titles, ingredients, instructions)
Images uploaded to recipes
Interactions (e.g., likes, saves)
Followers / social connections (“guests” and “kitchens” system)

3.4 Usage Data
We may collect information about how you use the App, including:
App screens viewed
Interactions with features (e.g., saving recipes)

3.5 Device and Technical Data
We may automatically collect:
Device type and model
Operating system version
Crash logs and error reports
IP address
App version

4. How We Use Your Data
We use your data to:
Provide and operate the Open Kitchen app
Create and manage user accounts
Display public profiles and recipes
Enable social features (followers, interactions)
Store and synchronize user-generated content
Improve app performance and user experience
Detect, prevent, and fix technical issues
Ensure security and prevent abuse

5. Firebase and Third-Party Services
We use the following third-party services provided by Google:
Firebase Authentication (user login and account management)
Cloud Firestore (data storage for recipes and profiles)
Firebase Cloud Storage (image storage)
Firebase Analytics (usage analysis, only if consent is given)
Firebase Crashlytics (crash reporting and stability monitoring)
Firebase App Check (security and abuse prevention) 
Firebase SQL connect (data storage for recipes and profiles)
These services may process your data on our behalf and may store data outside the European Economic Area (EEA).

6. Analytics and Consent
We use Firebase Analytics only if you provide consent.
You can:
Enable or disable analytics tracking at any time in the app settings
Analytics data is used to:
Understand how users interact with the App
Improve features and performance

7. Advertising
Open Kitchen does not use advertising or third-party ad networks.

8. Data Sharing
We do not sell your personal data.
We may share data only with:
Google Firebase services (for app functionality and infrastructure)
Legal authorities if required by law

9. Data Retention
We retain your data only as long as necessary:
Account data: until account deletion
Recipes and content: until deleted by the user or account removal
Analytics data: according to Firebase retention policies and consent settings
Crash reports: for debugging and stability purposes
You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time.

10. Your Rights Under GDPR
If you are located in the European Union, you have the following rights:
Right to access your data
Right to correct inaccurate data
Right to request deletion (“right to be forgotten”)
Right to restrict processing
Right to data portability
Right to withdraw consent (where applicable)
To exercise these rights, contact: support@healthyapp.info

11. Data Security
We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data, including:
Authentication systems
Access control mechanisms
Secure communication with backend services
However, no system can guarantee absolute security.

12. Children’s Privacy
Open Kitchen is not intended for children under 13 (or the applicable age of digital consent in your country). We do not knowingly collect data from children.

13. International Data Transfers
Your data may be processed outside the European Economic Area (EEA), including by Google Firebase infrastructure. Where required, appropriate safeguards are applied in accordance with GDPR.

14. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
Changes will be published within the App and become effective upon publication.

15. Contact
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, contact:
Healthy App Email: support@healthyapp.info
